page.title: 06WILDLIFE
page.content: Many animals can be seen on the river banks and woodlands in {LIFTON}such as squirrels,water voles,mice,minks otters.There is a large badgers set in A3.They cause considerable dammage to produce.The house where the badgers are seen belongs to Mrs Whitford.She puts food out on the window sill and watches the badgers come to feed. Many types of birds can be seen in { {DEVON}like the heron,dippers and kingfishers.Birds of prey are the other kinds of birds.Owls are nocturnal birds and come out at night. Also there is a disused quarry stocked with rainbow trout.Fish are abound in the local rivers. There is a pumping station in the { {LIFTON}area.And an organic Farm.
